Acronyms, initialisms, proper nouns, or any other word that has capitalization
rules in written English are subject to naming conventions just like any other
word. Even acronyms that are only 2 letters long are subject to these
conventions. File names fall into two categories: types and namespaces. If the file
(implicitly a struct) has top level fields, it should be named like any
other struct with fields using `TitleCase` . Otherwise,
it should use `snake_case` . Directory names should be `snake_case` . These are general rules of thumb; if it makes sense to do something different,
do what makes sense. For example, if there is an established convention such as `ENOENT` , follow the established convention. ### Examples §

